headline: Biggest Gains in Financial Strength in the Management Top 250
summary: Companies are graded in five categories: customer satisfaction, innovation, social responsibility, employee engagement and development, and financial strength.  The statistical model that produces the ranking was created by researchers at Claremont Graduate University’s Drucker Institute.  Bendable Labs, a private firm, works with Drucker to perform the calculations and interpret them.
